stylometry: When determining the total cost of managing a product you must take a few things into consideration.  You must know the reorder point and the EOQ (Economic Order Quantity).  The costs that you must consider are the cost of the inventory, ordering cost, and holding cost.  The costs you are balancing are the ordering and holding cost in regards to do you want to order more and hold more in inventory or order less and hold less in inventory.  Depending on the demand of the product will give you an idea to how much you want to order because you do not want to have wasted shelf space but at the same time you do not want to run out of the product relatively fast.
